description:
Round 2 gap analysis: Missed because the function looks reasonable at first glance.

At lines 140-143:
```c
static inline const char *lichen_link_strerror(int err)
{
    if (err >= 0) {
        return "success";
    }
```

The function is documented as 'Convert LICHEN link error code to human-readable string'. However, returning 'success' for any positive value is technically incorrect - positive values from lichen_link_rx/tx indicate byte counts, not success status.

In practice this is harmless because callers only call strerror on error paths (ret < 0). But the function contract is misleading - it should document that the function is only meaningful for negative values.

Very minor documentation issue.
